  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Dear Sir/Madam,  
I am sorry to hear of the way you were treated when you visited our x-ray department. I am particularly sorry to read that your situation was not handled in a caring and understanding way.  
Unfortunatley, our Trust Policy states that we are unable to use relatives for any interpretation that requires more than basic instructions. As video urodynamics is an invasive and undignified procedure, it requires more detail than basic instructions. I do appreciate that this could have been communicated to you more effectively and your feedback has already been shared with the department.  
I do understand your frustrations. As we cannot identify your Mother from your post or how to contact you, can I please suggest that you contact our PALS team on 0208 869 5118 or LNWH-tr.PALS@nhs.net. They will be able to help rebook your Mother's appointment and with an interpreter this time.  
Please accept my apologies once again.  
Best wishes  
Anjali Patel  
Patient Experience Manager&lt;/CommentText&gt;
